    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-09-14T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-09-14T16:00:00-05:00" n="105"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d105">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/9–1453: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-09-14T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 14, 1953—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 2. Attendance of alien <gloss
                        target="#t_NGOs1">NGO</gloss> representatives at United Nations General
                    Assembly.</p>
                <p>Regarding <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> telegram number 174, September
                    10, United Nations <gloss target="#t_NGOs1">NGO</gloss> section, in requesting
                    status report regarding visa application Reverend <persName corresp="#p_SCOTTM1"
                        >Michael Scott</persName>, advised <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss>
                    today that <persName corresp="#p_SCOTTM1">Scott</persName> only alien <gloss
                        target="#t_NGOs1">NGO</gloss> representative formally designated to attend
                    8th General Assembly.</p>
                <p>United Nations notified by <gloss target="#t_WFTU1">WFTU</gloss> that, because of
                        <gloss target="#t_WFTU1">WFTU</gloss> Congress meeting Vienna in October, no
                    representative would be sent from abroad to attend General Assembly and that
                        <gloss target="#t_WFTU1">WFTU</gloss> would be represented here by
                        <persName>Eleanor Kahn</persName>. United Nations in receipt some
                    correspondence from Congress of Canadian women, affiliate of <gloss
                        target="#t_WIDF1">WIDF</gloss>, implying Mrs. <persName
                        corresp="#p_LUCKOCKMR1">Margaretta Luckock</persName> might attend Session
                    as <gloss target="#t_WIDF1">WIDF</gloss> representative, but as yet no such
                    designation received from <gloss target="#t_WIDF1">WIDF</gloss>.</p>
                <p>In view foregoing, <persName corresp="#p_SCOTTM1">Scott</persName> may be only
                        <gloss target="#t_NGOs1">NGO</gloss> visa case this General Assembly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
